Source: pg-byteamagic
Section: database
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Ruohang Feng <rh@vonng.com>
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13), postgresql-all (>= 217~), libmagic-dev
Standards-Version: 4.6.2
Rules-Requires-Root: no
Homepage: https://github.com/nmandery/pg_byteamagic

Package: postgresql-PGVERSION-pg-byteamagic
Architecture: any
Provides: postgresql-pg-byteamagic
Depends: ${postgresql:Depends}, ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Breaks: ${postgresql:Breaks}
Description: Detect MIME types and file formats from PostgreSQL bytea values
  pg_byteamagic exposes the libmagic database to PostgreSQL through the
  byteamagic extension, allowing SQL queries to inspect a bytea value and
  return either its MIME type or a human-readable file type description.
